thread from where we left off.

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:56.010
And so just to remind you, the
Bohr model is for a 1-electron

00:02:56.010 --> 00:02:58.020
atom gas phase.

00:02:58.020 --> 00:03:01.280
So this is either atomic
hydrogen, it could be helium

00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:07.380
plus lithium 2 plus roentgenium
110 plus Its

00:03:07.380 --> 00:03:08.830
doesn't matter how
many protons.

00:03:08.830 --> 00:03:11.390
there's always only
want electron.

00:03:11.390 --> 00:03:13.500
And it's a planetary model.

00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:16.360
The positive charge concentrated
in the nucleus, Z

00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:18.160
is the proton number.

00:03:18.160 --> 00:03:22.910
And at a distance r from the
nucleus is a circular orbit in

00:03:22.910 --> 00:03:25.075
which resides 1 electron.

00:03:25.075 --> 00:03:27.780
It has a charge of minus E.

00:03:27.780 --> 00:03:30.180
And I just designated
them q1 and q2.

00:03:30.180 --> 00:03:31.360
You could have done
it the other way.

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:33.060
But I had to choose something.

00:03:33.060 --> 00:03:34.590
So we went through
and looked at the

00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:35.950
constitutive equations here.

00:03:35.950 --> 00:03:38.670
So first of all, the energy
of the system--

00:03:38.670 --> 00:03:40.960
and this is only going to be
the energy the electron.

00:03:40.960 --> 00:03:45.480
Because we assume that the
nucleus is far more massive.

00:03:45.480 --> 00:03:48.100
And so we don't have to get into
things like reduced mass

00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:48.830
or anything like that.

00:03:48.830 --> 00:03:51.430
So just measure the energy
of the electron.

00:03:51.430 --> 00:03:54.210
1/2 mv squared is the
newtonian component.

00:03:54.210 --> 00:03:59.910
And then coulombic energy that's
stored is z times e

00:03:59.910 --> 00:04:04.140
squared over 4 pi epsilon zero
r, where epsilon zero is the

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:05.430
permittivity of vacuum.

00:04:05.430 --> 00:04:09.160
And it's the factor, the 4 pi
epsilon zero, is the factor

00:04:09.160 --> 00:04:12.240
that allows us to take
electrostatic energies and put

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:16.525
them on the same plane as
mechanical energies.

00:04:16.525 --> 00:04:19.700
When we run through this, we
always end up in joules.

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:22.480
Then there's a force balanced to
make sure that the electron

00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:25.890
neither falls into the
nucleus nor flees and

00:04:25.890 --> 00:04:29.490
breaks free of the atom.

00:04:29.490 --> 00:04:32.560
And the force balance is if you
put a ball at the end of a

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:35.830
string, and you whip it around
on a tether, you have a

00:04:35.830 --> 00:04:38.040
centrifugal force that's trying
to get the ball to

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:38.760
break away.

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:41.260
And then the string
is pulling in.

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:45.270
So the pull in, in this case,
is the coulombic force.

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:49.340
And the force that makes the
ball want to flee is this mv

00:04:49.340 --> 00:04:50.360
squared over r.

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:52.510
And that must be net zero.

00:04:52.510 --> 00:04:55.380
Otherwise we're going to
have a shift in orbit.

00:04:55.380 --> 00:04:57.530
And then lastly we have
the quantum condition.

00:04:57.530 --> 00:05:02.270
And this was the breakthrough
of Bohr where he enunciated

00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:06.910
that the quantum condition is
going to give us this energy

00:05:06.910 --> 00:05:08.500
level quantization.

00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:12.010
And this was a big departure
from what had been in the

00:05:12.010 --> 00:05:16.150
past. The only antecedent idea
of this nature was the work by

00:05:16.150 --> 00:05:18.700
Planck who said that
light is quantized.

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:20.900
But as I told you last
day, who knows what

00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:22.070
light really is.

00:05:22.070 --> 00:05:26.040
The Newtonian notion of
a ball orbiting was

00:05:26.040 --> 00:05:27.780
very compelling here.

00:05:27.780 --> 00:05:32.690
And the notion that the movement
of the electron could

00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:37.380
in some way be discontinuous was
quite a major departure.

00:05:37.380 --> 00:05:38.790
So I left you last
day with three

00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:40.420
equations and three unknowns.

00:05:40.420 --> 00:05:42.370
And what I'm not going
to do right now

00:05:42.370 --> 00:05:44.080
is solve the equations.

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:46.390
Because I've been lecturing long
enough to know that's the

00:05:46.390 --> 00:05:49.530
way to kill interest,
quench a lecture.

00:05:49.530 --> 00:05:52.570
And so if you really want to go
through the algebra, be my

00:05:52.570 --> 00:05:54.250
guest. You're smart
enough to do that.

00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:55.650
Instead I'm going to show
you the results.

00:05:55.650 --> 00:05:57.790
But those are the three
equations that you need.

00:05:57.790 --> 00:05:59.650
So we have an equation in r.

00:05:59.650 --> 00:06:01.960
We have an equation at v,
and an equation in e.

00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:03.430
So let's go after them.

00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:07.020
If you first look at
the solution for r.

00:06:07.020 --> 00:06:10.640
This is the radius of the orbit
of the electron, the

00:06:10.640 --> 00:06:11.805
orbit of the electron.

00:06:11.805 --> 00:06:15.960
If you go through and solve,
you'll end up with this,

00:06:15.960 --> 00:06:19.980
Epsilon zero times the square of
the Planck constant divided

00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:22.720
by pi times m.

00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:23.920
It's always the electron.

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:26.530
So this is the radius of
the electron orbit.

00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:29.870
This is the mass of the electron
times the square of

00:06:29.870 --> 00:06:31.840
the elementary charge--

00:06:31.840 --> 00:06:33.730
that whole thing I'm
going to group--

00:06:33.730 --> 00:06:37.540
times the square of the quantum
number divided by z,

00:06:37.540 --> 00:06:39.720
the proton number.

00:06:39.720 --> 00:06:41.050
So what we see here?

00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:45.640
Well, everything inside the
parentheses is constant.

00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:46.440
These are all constant.

00:06:46.440 --> 00:06:48.750
Pi obviously is geometric
constant.

00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:50.970
And the rest of these are
constants you could look up in

00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:52.790
your table of constants.

00:06:52.790 --> 00:06:56.710
And we noticed that there is
a set of solutions to this.

00:06:56.710 --> 00:07:01.260
The radius of the electron can
occupy various discrete values

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:03.100
defined by n.

00:07:03.100 --> 00:07:06.680
So we say that the radius takes
on a plurality of values

00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:08.550
a function of n.

00:07:08.550 --> 00:07:12.170
And furthermore, the
functionality goes as the

00:07:12.170 --> 00:07:12.910
square of n.

00:07:12.910 --> 00:07:16.330
It's n squared times a constant,
where that constant

00:07:16.330 --> 00:07:18.770
is inside those parentheses.

00:07:18.770 --> 00:07:21.310
And we notice that because
the r goes as n

00:07:21.310 --> 00:07:23.670
squared it's nonlinear.

00:07:23.670 --> 00:07:24.920
It's nonlinear.

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:30.350
This is so important I'm
going to write it

00:07:30.350 --> 00:07:31.280
down one more time.

00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:41.725
So the radius of the electron
orbit takes multiple values.

00:07:41.725 --> 00:07:43.310
It takes multiple values.

00:07:46.490 --> 00:07:49.280
And they're discreet.

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:51.540
The physicists like to
use a different term.

00:07:51.540 --> 00:07:53.070
When something is
discretized, the

00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:56.540
physicists say it is quantized.

00:07:56.540 --> 00:07:58.380
So these values are quantized.

00:07:58.380 --> 00:08:07.610
You cannot continuously vary
the radius and nonlinear

00:08:07.610 --> 00:08:12.280
values, multiple values.

00:08:12.280 --> 00:08:15.900
So let's plug in.

00:08:15.900 --> 00:08:17.990
Because I want to get
a sense of scale.

00:08:17.990 --> 00:08:21.280
So let's look at the
simplest one.

00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:24.115
The most primitive 1-electron
atom would be hydrogen.

00:08:24.115 --> 00:08:26.280
In which case, Z equals 1.

00:08:26.280 --> 00:08:29.870
So I've just got a proton
orbited by an electron.

00:08:29.870 --> 00:08:35.170
So look at atomic hydrogen.

00:08:35.170 --> 00:08:38.950
So in that case, Z equals 1.

00:08:38.950 --> 00:08:42.790
And I'm going to look at n
equals 1, which is the lowest

00:08:42.790 --> 00:08:43.710
number here, right?

00:08:43.710 --> 00:08:45.120
R scales as n squared.

00:08:45.120 --> 00:08:49.130
So the lowest value or r is
obtained when n equals 1.

00:08:49.130 --> 00:08:52.230
And this is termed
the ground state.

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:55.560
The ground state.

00:08:55.560 --> 00:09:01.210
So I want to ask what is the
radius of the electron orbit

00:09:01.210 --> 00:09:03.280
ground state in atomic
hydrogen?

00:09:03.280 --> 00:09:07.265
And if I plug in these values,
I'll call this r sub 1.

00:09:07.265 --> 00:09:16.590
It turns out to be 5.29 times 10
to the minus 11 meters, or

00:09:16.590 --> 00:09:22.390
0.529 angstroms. I love
the angstrom.

00:09:22.390 --> 00:09:23.640
It's a great unit.

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:24.580
It's a great unit.

00:09:24.580 --> 00:09:26.460
It's not an SI unit.

00:09:26.460 --> 00:09:28.450
But I like the angstrom.

00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:29.510
I'll show you why.

00:09:29.510 --> 00:09:34.410
If you try to express this in
SI units, well there's 10 to

00:09:34.410 --> 00:09:36.990
the minus 11 meters.

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:43.340
The Si units go in units
of clusters of 1,000.

00:09:43.340 --> 00:09:45.200
So for example, you've
got the meter.

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:46.660
You've got the kilometer.

00:09:46.660 --> 00:09:48.230
You've got the micrometer.

00:09:48.230 --> 00:09:51.160
You've got 10 to the
minus 9 meters,

00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:53.650
which is the nanometer.

00:09:56.250 --> 00:09:57.520
This is a Goldilocks problem.

00:09:57.520 --> 00:09:58.320
This one's too big.

00:09:58.320 --> 00:10:01.330
And then the next one down here
is 10 to the minus 12

00:10:01.330 --> 00:10:03.350
meters, which is
the picometer.

00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:07.960
So this is either 52.9
picometers, or a 0.0529

00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:09.970
nanometers.

00:10:09.970 --> 00:10:11.000
And that's no good.

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:14.930
I want numbers like 3, 7,
simple to remember.

00:10:14.930 --> 00:10:20.740
So 0.529, this is about
1/2 angstrom.

00:10:20.740 --> 00:10:21.910
It's good to know.

00:10:21.910 --> 00:10:24.280
But you try to publish, you
know what happens in a

00:10:24.280 --> 00:10:25.910
scientific literature today?

00:10:25.910 --> 00:10:28.710
The Literary Lions that control
the journals, they'll

00:10:28.710 --> 00:10:31.510
circle that and say you have
to convert to SI units.

00:10:31.510 --> 00:10:32.930
And so they have to
right some goofy

00:10:32.930 --> 00:10:34.680
nanometer thing or something.

00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:37.430
I know you think I'm crazy,
but I love the angstrom.

00:10:37.430 --> 00:10:38.100
So there.

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.890
Anyway, so here it is.

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:43.770
Once you know that this is
0.529, this is on your table

00:10:43.770 --> 00:10:44.660
of constants.

00:10:44.660 --> 00:10:46.550
It's right on your table
of constants.

00:10:46.550 --> 00:10:48.880
So you don't have to go and
calculate all this stuff.

00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:52.110
Which means if you do your
homework with your table of

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:56.080
constants, you will know where
those numbers lie, as opposed

00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:59.450
to opening this thing up for
the first time on the first

00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:02.800
celebration of learning on
October the 7th, and with 47

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:04.910
entries and they're
tiny, tiny font.

00:11:04.910 --> 00:11:08.060
And you're wondering where
is that thing.

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:09.140
Just a word to wise.

00:11:09.140 --> 00:11:10.860
So now we know what this is.

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:14.650
We know this is 0.529 angstroms.
So now I can write

00:11:14.650 --> 00:11:17.770
an equation for the radius
of a 1-electron

00:11:17.770 --> 00:11:20.330
atom anywhere, anytime.

00:11:20.330 --> 00:11:26.600
r of n is going to be equal
to a naught which

00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:29.620
is this value here.

00:11:29.620 --> 00:11:31.460
And it is termed the
Bohr radius.

00:11:34.790 --> 00:11:37.050
So you can write it as a
function of the Bohr radius,

00:11:37.050 --> 00:11:41.750
times the square of
n divided by Z.

00:11:41.750 --> 00:11:45.230
So that's for all 1-electron
atoms, gas phase.

00:11:45.230 --> 00:11:50.930
And you can see that as Z goes
up, the r goes down, which

00:11:50.930 --> 00:11:51.520
makes sense.

00:11:51.520 --> 00:11:56.100
So suppose instead of hydrogen,
we talk helium plus

00:11:56.100 --> 00:11:57.020
What's the only difference?

00:11:57.020 --> 00:11:59.580
Helium plus has 2 protons
in the nucleus.

00:11:59.580 --> 00:12:03.090
Which means that the coulombic
force of attraction between

00:12:03.090 --> 00:12:07.010
the same 1-electron and now a
doubly charged nucleus is

00:12:07.010 --> 00:12:09.340
going to be stronger.

00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.320
So the first orbit is going
to get pulled in.

00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:14.210
And all the other orbits are
going to get pulled in.

00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:16.200
By how much are they going
to get pulled in?

00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:17.100
By that much.

00:12:17.100 --> 00:12:19.900
So this is the functional
representation

00:12:19.900 --> 00:12:21.730
of all of that physics.

00:12:21.730 --> 00:12:23.540
All right, there's three
equations, three unknowns.

00:12:23.540 --> 00:12:24.930
Let's look at energy.

00:12:24.930 --> 00:12:27.960
So if you go through and solve
for energy, you get this one.

00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:31.840
Minus this big monstrosity, mass
of the electron to the

00:12:31.840 --> 00:12:37.390
fourth power of the elementary
charge times 8 times the

00:12:37.390 --> 00:12:41.470
square of the permittivity of
vacuum times the square of the

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:47.740
Planck constant, all times the
square of the Proton number

00:12:47.740 --> 00:12:52.630
divided by the square of
the quantum number.

00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:56.080
And I just to make sure
everybody is with me here.

00:12:56.080 --> 00:13:01.430
I always want to write n here.
n equals 1, 2, 3, takes on

00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:02.710
integer values.

00:13:02.710 --> 00:13:04.090
And we'll say it again here.

00:13:04.090 --> 00:13:08.530
N equals 1, 2, 3, et
cetera, et cetera.

00:13:08.530 --> 00:13:15.020
So again we say we see that
e is a function of n.

00:13:15.020 --> 00:13:15.720
It's discretized.

00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:17.890
It's quantized.

00:13:17.890 --> 00:13:18.580
Why?

00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:22.330
Because once you impose the
quantum condition here on

00:13:22.330 --> 00:13:24.470
angular momentum, it propagates

00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:25.880
through the entire model.

00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:28.470
So radius this quantized, energy
is quantized, you're

00:13:28.470 --> 00:13:29.970
going to see velocity
is quantized.

00:13:29.970 --> 00:13:33.740
Because the quantum condition
is pervasive.

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:38.110
So e to the n, and I'm going to
take this whole quantity in

00:13:38.110 --> 00:13:42.810
parentheses and just
call it giant K.

00:13:42.810 --> 00:13:44.600
These are all positive
quantities.

00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:45.720
Mass is positive.

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:49.010
And squares and fourth powers
of numbers must be positive.

00:13:49.010 --> 00:13:56.650
So this is K times Z squared
over n squared That's good.

00:13:56.650 --> 00:13:59.210
And we can go and evaluate K.

00:13:59.210 --> 00:14:05.990
And when we evaluate L in SI
units, we get 2.18 times 10 to

00:14:05.990 --> 00:14:10.500
the minus 18 joules.

00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:13.450
This is joules per atom.

00:14:13.450 --> 00:14:16.750
Or you can multiply this
by Avogadro's number.

00:14:16.750 --> 00:14:19.230
If you multiply it by Avogadro's
number, then that

00:14:19.230 --> 00:14:28.270
will give you 1.312 megajoules
per mol.

00:14:28.270 --> 00:14:32.700
So that's the energy of the
electron in the ground state

00:14:32.700 --> 00:14:34.730
of atomic hydrogen.

00:14:34.730 --> 00:14:39.000
And then we can mediate that
with Z and n, and go to

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.870
electrons that are outside the
ground state, above the ground

00:14:41.870 --> 00:14:45.160
state, or ground state electrons
in atoms that have

00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:47.800
more than 1 proton, or both.

00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:50.630
And so let's take a look
at the graphical

00:14:50.630 --> 00:14:51.790
representation of that.

00:14:51.790 --> 00:14:55.030
So instead of Cartesian
coordinates, because this is

00:14:55.030 --> 00:14:57.450
spatial distribution, I'm
going to go to energy

00:14:57.450 --> 00:15:00.080
coordinates and give you an
energy level diagram.

00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:05.700
So again, not to scale.

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:08.940
Because this thing goes
is 1 over the square.

00:15:08.940 --> 00:15:10.300
So that's going to be messy.

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:12.360
So let's start here.

00:15:12.360 --> 00:15:15.535
And on the left side I'm going
to designate the energy.

00:15:15.535 --> 00:15:17.590
And on the right side
I'm going to

00:15:17.590 --> 00:15:18.950
designate the quantum number.

00:15:18.950 --> 00:15:20.280
I'm going to start down here.

00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:21.470
That's the lowest energy.

00:15:21.470 --> 00:15:23.810
You see these are all negative
values, first of all.

00:15:23.810 --> 00:15:25.670
They're all negative values.

00:15:25.670 --> 00:15:27.910
Because Z is a square,
n is a square, and K

00:15:27.910 --> 00:15:29.750
is a positive quantity.

00:15:29.750 --> 00:15:31.600
So n equals 1 is the
lowest state.

00:15:31.600 --> 00:15:32.770
It's the ground state.

00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:37.680
It has a value of minus K.

00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:40.660
So I'm going to do this one
just for atomic hydrogen.

00:15:40.660 --> 00:15:44.440
So I'm going to write
atomic H.

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:47.900
So now Z equals 1.

00:15:47.900 --> 00:15:51.520
You can do it later for Z
equals 2, 3, whatever.

00:15:51.520 --> 00:15:52.850
So this is atomic hydrogen.

00:15:52.850 --> 00:15:56.580
So ground state energy
is minus K.

00:15:56.580 --> 00:15:59.700
What happens if we go to n
equals 2? n equals 2 it

00:15:59.700 --> 00:16:02.460
becomes K divided
by 2 squared 4.

00:16:02.460 --> 00:16:04.000
So it should be 3/4
of the way up.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:06.180
I'm not going to go quite
3/4 of the way.

00:16:06.180 --> 00:16:08.710
Because I want to leave room
for some fine structure.

00:16:08.710 --> 00:16:10.380
That's why it's not to scale.

00:16:10.380 --> 00:16:13.200
All right so this is
minus L over 4.

00:16:13.200 --> 00:16:15.060
What if we go to n equals 3?

00:16:15.060 --> 00:16:16.430
Well it's not symmetric here.

00:16:16.430 --> 00:16:17.150
It's nonlinear.

00:16:17.150 --> 00:16:18.940
But this should be
really what?

00:16:18.940 --> 00:16:21.880
Minus K over 3 squared is 9.

00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:22.720
You get the picture.

00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:27.170
3, you can go 4, 5, and so on
until n equals infinity.

00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:29.450
What happens when n
equals infinity?

00:16:29.450 --> 00:16:33.210
I've got minus K over infinity,
which is vanishingly

00:16:33.210 --> 00:16:34.840
small, zero.

00:16:34.840 --> 00:16:38.590
Where is the electron when
n equals infinity?

00:16:38.590 --> 00:16:42.740
r is n squared times
the Bohr radius.

00:16:42.740 --> 00:16:46.830
That's a great, great
distance away.

00:16:46.830 --> 00:16:47.870
What does it mean?

00:16:47.870 --> 00:16:50.810
Physically it means that the
electron is so far away that

00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:52.190
it is no longer bound.

00:16:52.190 --> 00:16:55.710
It's no longer part
of the atom.

00:16:55.710 --> 00:16:58.910
And when it's no longer part of
the atom, and the potential

00:16:58.910 --> 00:17:01.920
energy that's stored is a result
of the charges coming

00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:03.630
together from infinity.

00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:05.800
I'm starting to talk like
someone out of 802.

00:17:05.800 --> 00:17:09.480
What's the energy if I take 2
charged particles at infinite

00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:10.210
separation?

00:17:10.210 --> 00:17:12.510
I bring them into some
finite separation.

00:17:12.510 --> 00:17:13.170
Voila.

00:17:13.170 --> 00:17:13.970
There it is.

00:17:13.970 --> 00:17:15.590
So when they're in infinite
separation

00:17:15.590 --> 00:17:17.030
there's no energy stored.

00:17:17.030 --> 00:17:18.850
Hence, you are at that point.

00:17:18.850 --> 00:17:25.000
So n equals infinity means r
equals infinity, which means E

00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:25.780
equal zero.

00:17:25.780 --> 00:17:27.590
There's no stored energy.

00:17:27.590 --> 00:17:30.570
So this means the electron
is no longer bound.

00:17:33.940 --> 00:17:37.080
And therefore, if it's
no longer bound, we

00:17:37.080 --> 00:17:37.930
have a term for it.

00:17:37.930 --> 00:17:39.440
It's called free.

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:42.290
It's a free electron.

00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:44.480
And if the electron
is free, then the

00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:48.565
atom is electron deficient.

00:17:48.565 --> 00:17:50.780
So if the electron is
free, that means the

00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:54.810
atom is now an ion.

00:17:54.810 --> 00:17:56.225
Because it's lost an electron.

00:17:56.225 --> 00:17:57.990
It's no longer net neutral.

00:17:57.990 --> 00:18:03.800
Or we say an atom hasn't
turned into an ion.

00:18:03.800 --> 00:18:06.200
Or the electron has
been ionized.

00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:14.130
What's the energy for that?

00:18:14.130 --> 00:18:15.740
We can calculate what
that energy is.

00:18:15.740 --> 00:18:17.760
It would be called the
ionization energy.

00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:20.620
So if I started with an electron
down in here, and I

00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:23.090
sent it all the way
to infinity.

00:18:23.090 --> 00:18:24.490
See that's an energy space.

00:18:24.490 --> 00:18:27.410
Which is the equivalent in
Cartesian space to go from

00:18:27.410 --> 00:18:30.510
here to infinity, same idea.

00:18:30.510 --> 00:18:32.040
Do you see the models?

00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:34.460
This is Cartesian.

00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:34.900
It's like a.

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:37.450
Map This is energy
coordinates.

00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:38.740
It's different.

00:18:38.740 --> 00:18:40.210
And you're going to be
able to think from

00:18:40.210 --> 00:18:41.600
one model to another.

00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:43.050
What's the energy
consequences?

00:18:43.050 --> 00:18:44.980
What are the Cartesian
consequences?

00:18:44.980 --> 00:18:46.980
Until we get to the point where
there is no Cartesian

00:18:46.980 --> 00:18:47.790
representation.

00:18:47.790 --> 00:18:50.560
Because the abstraction level
is too high, we'll have to

00:18:50.560 --> 00:18:51.720
content ourselves with this.

00:18:51.720 --> 00:18:54.000
So get comfortable moving
from there to there.

00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:56.550
And then some day we're going
to say it's too complicated.

00:18:56.550 --> 00:18:58.240
There's no Cartesian thing.

00:18:58.240 --> 00:18:59.800
We'll be comfortable
by then with this.

00:18:59.800 --> 00:19:02.580
OK so now we're taking an
electron from here up to here.

00:19:02.580 --> 00:19:06.600
While we ask, what is the
ionization energy?

00:19:06.600 --> 00:19:10.370
The ionization energy must
equal the delta E of the

00:19:10.370 --> 00:19:11.620
transition.

00:19:14.440 --> 00:19:15.230
So what's that?

00:19:15.230 --> 00:19:18.560
The delta E of the transition
is going to equal always E

00:19:18.560 --> 00:19:22.360
final minus E initial.

00:19:22.360 --> 00:19:25.290
E final minus E initial.

00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:29.530
Which is equal to E
at infinity minus

00:19:29.530 --> 00:19:32.000
E1, the ground state.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:34.540
Well E infinity, we just
said, is zero.

00:19:34.540 --> 00:19:38.630
And the ground state energy
is equal to minus K.

00:19:38.630 --> 00:19:40.860
So minus minus K is K.

00:19:40.860 --> 00:19:44.120
So you also get the energy.

00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:47.090
From infinity down to
ground state is

00:19:47.090 --> 00:19:48.960
the ionization energy.

00:19:48.960 --> 00:19:58.050
So we can define the ionization
energy in terms of

00:19:58.050 --> 00:19:59.610
this transition.

00:19:59.610 --> 00:20:06.280
Define ionization energy as the
minimum energy to remove

00:20:06.280 --> 00:20:23.430
an electron from the
ground state of an

00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:24.733
atom in a gas phase.

00:20:31.020 --> 00:20:32.640
So that means there's no
solids, no liquids.

00:20:32.640 --> 00:20:33.980
There's no work function here.

00:20:33.980 --> 00:20:36.410
There's no lattice energy,
and so on.

00:20:36.410 --> 00:20:40.340
So there's a definition of
the ionization energy.

00:20:40.340 --> 00:20:42.880
And we can be a little
bit more elaborate.

00:20:42.880 --> 00:20:44.300
Even though right now I'm
just going to do a

00:20:44.300 --> 00:20:45.380
little break here.

00:20:45.380 --> 00:20:46.620
I don't want to mislead
people.

00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:49.620
But just an aside.

00:20:49.620 --> 00:20:51.110
I'm nonlinear.

00:20:51.110 --> 00:20:53.070
I can have multiple
conversations at once.

00:20:53.070 --> 00:20:54.910
And you are capable
of stacking.

00:20:54.910 --> 00:20:56.130
So we're going to break now.

00:20:56.130 --> 00:20:58.160
We're not going to talk
about 1-electron atom.

00:20:58.160 --> 00:21:01.900
We're going to follow the thread
of ionization energy.

00:21:01.900 --> 00:21:03.310
I'm going to take lithium.

00:21:03.310 --> 00:21:08.250
Lithium in its normal state has
3 protons, 3 electrons.

00:21:08.250 --> 00:21:10.140
So I'm going to take
lithium gas.

00:21:10.140 --> 00:21:13.800
And I'm going to ionize it
and make lithium plus.

00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:16.230
So this is a lithium plus
ion in the gas phase.

00:21:16.230 --> 00:21:17.760
It's still got 2 electrons.

00:21:17.760 --> 00:21:19.330
So this isn't Bohr
model stuff.

00:21:19.330 --> 00:21:21.880
But anyway, here we are.

00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:26.470
So the energy for this action
would be called

00:21:26.470 --> 00:21:27.690
the ionization energy.

00:21:27.690 --> 00:21:31.437
Because I took a neutral atom,
and I pulled an electron out

00:21:31.437 --> 00:21:32.910
of the ground state,
and so on.

00:21:32.910 --> 00:21:34.140
So this is an ionization
energy.

00:21:34.140 --> 00:21:36.790
But now I can continue
this process.

00:21:36.790 --> 00:21:39.860
And I can take Lithium plus.

00:21:39.860 --> 00:21:42.900
And I can lose an electron from
that, which will than

00:21:42.900 --> 00:21:45.970
give me lithium 2 plus.

00:21:45.970 --> 00:21:48.150
And this is called also
an ionization energy.

00:21:48.150 --> 00:21:50.710
This is called the second
ionization energy.

00:21:50.710 --> 00:21:52.320
So this is the first
ionization energy.

00:21:52.320 --> 00:21:55.650
But just as when you write an
equation, when the coefficient

00:21:55.650 --> 00:21:59.450
is 1, you don't write the 1.

00:21:59.450 --> 00:22:01.110
I don't write 1 lithium here.

00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:02.360
I know it's 1.

00:22:02.360 --> 00:22:04.460
This is the second ionization
energy.

00:22:04.460 --> 00:22:06.700
And then I can keep stripping
away electrons.

00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:11.010
And I can take lithium 2 plus
in the gas phase, and take

00:22:11.010 --> 00:22:16.120
away that electron leaving me
with just the lithium nucleus,

00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:19.060
lithium 3 plus, plus electron.

00:22:19.060 --> 00:22:23.260
And that's called the third
ionization energy.

00:22:23.260 --> 00:22:25.340
OK, now what can we say?

00:22:25.340 --> 00:22:29.530
What's the relationship here
between any of this except the

00:22:29.530 --> 00:22:31.860
definition and the Bohr model?

00:22:31.860 --> 00:22:32.250
well?

00:22:32.250 --> 00:22:35.810
The Bohr model applies only to
1-electron atoms. Are there

00:22:35.810 --> 00:22:40.270
any 1-electron atoms
on this board?

00:22:40.270 --> 00:22:42.460
So we can calculate
the energy, the

00:22:42.460 --> 00:22:43.820
third ionization energy.

00:22:43.820 --> 00:22:45.730
We can get that from
the Bohr model.

00:22:48.330 --> 00:22:49.820
You can do it in your head.

00:22:49.820 --> 00:22:51.360
You can do it in your
head right?

00:22:51.360 --> 00:22:55.520
It's just K times Z squared
right here.

00:22:55.520 --> 00:22:56.630
It's going from 1.

00:22:56.630 --> 00:23:02.480
So if this is 2.18, it's going
to be 9 times that trivially.

00:23:02.480 --> 00:23:08.040
OK, so this is just
3 squared times K.

00:23:08.040 --> 00:23:11.860
And this when you have to
get from the literature.

00:23:11.860 --> 00:23:14.000
So you have to go to
primary sources.

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:15.060
Which is why you're going
to learn how to

00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:17.530
use the proper database.

00:23:17.530 --> 00:23:20.070
And this one here also you
get from the literature.

00:23:20.070 --> 00:23:23.020
But this is on your
periodic table.

00:23:23.020 --> 00:23:26.040
Your periodic table, one of the
data points it gives is

00:23:26.040 --> 00:23:28.960
the first ionization energy
of all of the elements.

00:23:28.960 --> 00:23:31.790
And so even though lithium
normally is a solid at room

00:23:31.790 --> 00:23:35.140
temperature, the ionization
energy for lithium as given on

00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:36.945
your periodic table is
for this reaction.

00:23:36.945 --> 00:23:40.100
It's for the gas.

00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:40.400
Anyway.

00:23:40.400 --> 00:23:42.660
So that's little aside.

00:23:42.660 --> 00:23:46.410
All right, the last quantity
that we could get from the

00:23:46.410 --> 00:23:49.690
Bohr model is v, the velocity.

00:23:49.690 --> 00:23:50.730
And I solve for the velocity.

00:23:50.730 --> 00:23:52.240
We don't talk about
this very much.

00:23:52.240 --> 00:23:56.950
But we're going to
do so once today.

00:23:56.950 --> 00:23:58.210
And here it is.

00:23:58.210 --> 00:23:59.820
So I went through the algebra.

00:23:59.820 --> 00:24:05.780
And you get nh over 2 pi mr,
where r is the radius.

00:24:05.780 --> 00:24:07.020
There's the quantum number.

00:24:07.020 --> 00:24:08.600
This is quantized as well.

00:24:08.600 --> 00:24:09.830
So I regrouped this.

00:24:09.830 --> 00:24:12.800
And I already have a nice, cool
expression for r in terms

00:24:12.800 --> 00:24:14.070
of the Bohr radius.

00:24:14.070 --> 00:24:16.910
So I use that because
that's on the table.

00:24:16.910 --> 00:24:20.690
So this is 2 pi times the mass
of the electron times the Bohr

00:24:20.690 --> 00:24:28.240
radius, 1/2 angstrom, times Z
proton number divided by n,

00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:32.810
where n equals 1,
2, 3, and so on.

00:24:32.810 --> 00:24:34.980
So let's again get
a sense of scale.

00:24:34.980 --> 00:24:38.160
So let's try for
sense of scale.

00:24:41.540 --> 00:24:45.950
Let's do velocity of the ground
state electron in

00:24:45.950 --> 00:24:47.350
atomic hydrogen.

00:24:47.350 --> 00:24:51.080
So that means Z equals
1, n equals 1.

00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:52.760
So I plug in the numbers.

00:24:52.760 --> 00:24:59.800
And I get v1 for hydrogen,
atomic hydrogen, gives me 2.18

00:24:59.800 --> 00:25:02.870
times 10 to the 6 meters
for second.

00:25:06.870 --> 00:25:07.180
I don't know.

00:25:07.180 --> 00:25:07.950
Is that fast?

00:25:07.950 --> 00:25:08.880
Is that slow?

00:25:08.880 --> 00:25:09.260
I don't know.

00:25:09.260 --> 00:25:10.490
But I do know this much.

00:25:10.490 --> 00:25:14.890
I know that the speed of light
is equal to 3 times 10 to the

00:25:14.890 --> 00:25:16.943
8 meters per second.

00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:24.080
So 10 to the 8 divided
by 10 to the 6.

00:25:24.080 --> 00:25:27.280
2 and 3, that's roughly 1,
speaking as an engineer.

00:25:27.280 --> 00:25:28.620
Who cares?

00:25:28.620 --> 00:25:32.540
So this is about 1% of
the speed of light.

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:36.790
That's pretty good.

00:25:36.790 --> 00:25:38.960
That gives me something
I can hang on to.

00:25:38.960 --> 00:25:42.900
I would say that if this thing
is zipping around at 1% of the

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:50.090
speed of light, I would say
that's relatively fast. One

00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:52.060
more time, 1% of the
speed of light.

00:25:52.060 --> 00:25:58.030
That's relatively fast.

00:25:58.030 --> 00:26:01.560
Remember last day I told you
that Bohr simply dismissed the

00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:06.850
concept of the use of classical
electrodynamics down

00:26:06.850 --> 00:26:08.270
to atomic dimensions.

00:26:08.270 --> 00:26:11.840
Well here's another example of
why a lot of these assumptions

00:26:11.840 --> 00:26:13.250
aren't going to work so well.

00:26:13.250 --> 00:26:17.330
We're talking about the ground
state electron velocity in

00:26:17.330 --> 00:26:21.140
this putative planetary model
of a 1-electron atom.

00:26:21.140 --> 00:26:23.010
You're already getting into
relativistic effects.

00:26:23.010 --> 00:26:25.120
So, just another example.

00:26:25.120 --> 00:26:29.592
By the way, why do we use the
